JOHANNESBURG - Pressure is mounting on MultiChoice's parent company, Naspers over its relationship with the Gupta family. Naspers investors have requested US law firm Pomerantz to investigate the company and its directors for unlawful business practices. READ: Multichoice, ANN7 deal: Government says 'no need' to get into the fray The investigation follows media reports that MultiChoice made improper payments to Gupta-linked TV channel ANN7. It's is alleged that it increased ANN7's annual payment from R50-million R141- million over two years. MultiChoice has denied any wrong doing. eNCA